{#-
  Relaxed Mistral/Mixtral [INST] chat template for AGENTIC multi-turn RL.

  Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct-v0.1's STOCK template enforces strict user/assistant
  alternation via `raise_exception(...)` and supports ONLY user/assistant roles.
  That breaks the SkyRL agentic pipeline in two ways:

    1. `encode_messages_subset` re-encodes ONE message at a time appended to a
       fixed base `[system, user]`. A `user` turn then yields `[user, user]`
       after the system strip -> the stock template's alternation assert raises
       (`conversation roles must alternate user/assistant/...`).
    2. Any consecutive same-role turn or a `tool`/observation message in a
       trajectory would hit the same assert / the role `raise_exception`.

  This template keeps Mixtral's NATIVE `[INST] ... [/INST]` + ` content</s>`
  format (so the model's instruction-tuned prior is preserved for cold-start)
  but:
    * DROPS the strict-alternation assertion entirely.
    * MERGES consecutive same-role turns into a single rendered block (so
      `[user, user]` from the fixed-base per-message encode renders as one
      `[INST] ... [/INST]`, and N consecutive assistant turns concatenate).
    * Serializes a `tool` (observation) message as a user-side `[INST]` block
      (folded into the surrounding user turn) so tool output is plain text the
      v1 tokenizer can represent (no v3 [TOOL_CALLS] special tokens — Mixtral's
      v1 vocab lacks them).

  LOSS-MASK CONTRACT (must match SkyRL get_response_ids_and_loss_mask_from_messages):
    * No `add_generation_prompt` suffix is emitted (Mixtral has none), so
      `get_generation_prompt_ids` returns [] and `prefix_len == 0` -> the entire
      ` content</s>` of an assistant turn is masked as generated (mask=1), with
      the EOS included. This mirrors the stock template's assistant rendering
      ` ` + content + eos_token EXACTLY, so the per-assistant-turn token slice
      (and therefore the TIS token-id alignment) is byte-identical to stock.
    * A user/tool turn renders WITHOUT eos -> masked 0, identical to stock.

  Roles handled: system (initial only, folded into first user [INST]),
  user, assistant, tool (folded as user-side observation text).
-#}
{%- if messages[0]['role'] == 'system' %}
    {%- set system_message = messages[0]['content'] %}
    {%- set loop_messages = messages[1:] %}
{%- else %}
    {%- set loop_messages = messages %}
{%- endif %}
{{- bos_token }}
{%- set ns = namespace(prev_role='none', system_emitted=false) %}
{%- for message in loop_messages %}
    {#- Normalize a `tool`/observation message to the user side. -#}
    {%- if message['role'] == 'assistant' %}
        {%- set cur_role = 'assistant' %}
    {%- else %}
        {%- set cur_role = 'user' %}
    {%- endif %}
    {%- if message['content'] is string %}
        {%- set content = message['content'] %}
    {%- else %}
        {%- set content = '' %}
    {%- endif %}
    {%- if cur_role == 'user' %}
        {#- Open a new [INST] block only when the previous rendered role was NOT
            user (merge consecutive user/tool turns into one block). -#}
        {%- if ns.prev_role != 'user' %}
            {%- if not ns.system_emitted and system_message is defined %}
                {{- ' [INST] ' + system_message + '\n\n' + content }}
                {%- set ns.system_emitted = true %}
            {%- else %}
                {{- ' [INST] ' + content }}
            {%- endif %}
        {%- else %}
            {#- Consecutive user/tool turn: append to the open [INST] block. -#}
            {{- '\n\n' + content }}
        {%- endif %}
    {%- else %}
        {#- assistant. Close any open [INST] block, then emit ` content</s>`.
            Consecutive assistant turns: the prior turn already wrote its eos,
            so just concatenate ` content</s>` again (mask logic re-masks each
            assistant turn independently via its own EOS). -#}
        {%- if ns.prev_role == 'user' %}
            {{- ' [/INST]' }}
        {%- endif %}
        {{- ' ' + content + eos_token }}
    {%- endif %}
    {%- set ns.prev_role = cur_role %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- if add_generation_prompt %}
    {#- Close a dangling user block so the model is prompted to answer. Stock
        Mixtral emits no extra generation tokens; we only need the [/INST]. -#}
    {%- if ns.prev_role == 'user' %}
        {{- ' [/INST]' }}
    {%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
